  “Femi Fani Kayode, the former minister of aviation has reacted to the plan by former factional chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Senator Ali Modu Sheriff to defect to the All Progressive Congress, APC.”   The leadership of the APC had on the report that Sheriff was set to join the Party, asked him to join from his ward..   Reacting, Fani Kayode blasted Sheriff, describing him as an ‘unconciable filth’ and a betrayal..   He stated that Sheriff will be crushed upon defection.   The former minister wrote “Thank God that the reprehensible reprobate and unconciable filth called Ali Modu Sheriff has finally crawled back to the hole that he came from..   “His name is synonomous with treachery and betrayal.   “History will savage him and posterity will strip him bare and crush him.”   Meanwhile, thirty-four State Chairmen under the defunct Ali Modu Sheriff-led caretaker committee of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), on Thursday formally defected to the All Progressives Congress (APC).”